Directory distribution_testing: contains Makefile scripts to test the latest ROI_PAC distribution

Needs the environment variables

TESTBENCH        (e.g. setenv TESTBENCH /RAID4/$USER/testbench ; set in local .cshrc file)
ROIPAC_TESTDATA  (e.g. setenv ROIPAC_TESTDATA "$INSARLABHOME/testdata/roi_pac" ; currently set in cshrc_SAR_CONFIG)

The scripts generate the appropriate data directories in $TESTBENCH and symbolic links to the data files
which are located in $ROIPAC_TESTDATA. The scripts are run in $TESTBENCH. All files are removed if the tests are succesful and run to the end

The default test directory is RSAT_vexint (Hawaii). This is specified in distribution_testing/Makefile. Different
testdata sets can be specified with the environment variable ROIPACTESTFLAG 
(e.g. setenv ROIPACTESTFLAG TESTDATASET=ERS_roi_pac). 

Testing is performed simply by calling    

make all

in the respective directories (e.g. in RSAT_vexint)

or by the following calls

make ERS_roi_pac
make RSAT_vexint
make ENVISAT_roi_pac
make RSAT_fromSLC
make RSAT_fromSLC_models

make process_rsmas_Env
make process_rsmas_multi_Env
make process_rsmas_Ers-esa

make NONE

if test succesful an interferogram is displayed when processing is complete.

Benchmarking 1 process_rsmas run
make process_rsmas_Env_time1

Benchmarking 1,2,4,8 runs in parallel:
make ERS_roi_pac_time1
make ERS_roi_pac_time2
make ERS_roi_pac_time4
make ERS_roi_pac_time5
make ERS_roi_pac_time6
make ERS_roi_pac_time7
make ERS_roi_pac_time8

make RSAT_vexint_time1
make RSAT_vexint_time2
make RSAT_vexint_time4
make RSAT_vexint_time8

to do all of them in one stretch:
make ERS_roi_pac_time
make RSAT_vexint_time

displays timing information for 1,2,4,8 parallel runs
############################################################################
ERS_roi_pac:    Long Valley ERS
RSAT_vexint:    Hawaii Radarsat
Envisat_roi_pac: LasVegas Radarsat
NONE:			 Non testting is done

